**Operating system or device - Godot version: Windows 10, Godot 2.1.2 stable **

Is it possible to pass functions through variables?

Similar as in Javascript like this:

var MakeRain = function MakeRain(){
  bunchOfCodesToMakeRain();
}

Map(MakeRain);

-----

Inside the Map:

function Map(dosomething)
{
  dosomething() //which will cast MakeRain, or any function.
}

Is this possible in Godot? Sending function as arguments.
